        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 15:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Officers and judges",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Hebrew ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "וְשֹׁמְרִים וְשֹׁפְטִים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The explanation of the nature of the work of these, as really outward work, for the \"outward business of Israel,\" is distinctly stated in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 26:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 19:5-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "officers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " are mentioned under the same Hebrew term in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 5:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in a very different connection. It is plain that they were generally foremen, or overseers; while the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "judges",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " took cognizance of matters which involved the interests of religion. This verse and the following give between them the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "four",
        "children": []
      },
      {
